transliteration: Sramit Bisan Tahh Rahat Samaaee|| Sindh Bindh Jah Gadyo Na Jaaee||
translation: Fatigued by his work, Vishnu remains merged in Him and within that Immanent Lord, there are unaccountable oceans and worlds.

transliteration: Sahansra Sees Tab Dhartan Janad|| Sahansra Paav Kar Sahans Abhanad||
translation: He hath thousands of heads, trunks and legs; He hath thousands of hands and feet; He, the Invincible Lord;

translation: The day on which Vishnu manifested himself for the killing of Madhu and Kaitabh,

transliteration: Sravan Mail Te Asur Prakaasat|| Channd Soor Jan Doutiya Prabhaasat||
translation: From the dross of the ear, the demons were born and were considered glorious like Chandra and Surya.

transliteration: Maayaa Tajat Bisan Kah Tab Hee|| Karat Oupaadh Asur Mil(i) Jab Hee||5||
translation: With the orders of the Immanent Lord, Vishnu abandoned maya and manifested himself at that time, when these demons indulged in riots.5.

gurmukhi: iqn soN krq ibsn Gmswnw ] brK hjwr pMc prmwnw ]
transliteration: Tin Son Karat Bisan Ghamsaana|| Barakh Hajaar Panch Parmaanaa||
translation: Vishnu waged ferocious war with them for five thousand years .

transliteration: Kaal Purakh Tab Hot Sahaaee|| Duhoonan(i) Hanta Krodh Ouphaaee||6||
translation: The Immanent Lord then helped Vishnu and in great fury, he destroyed both the demons.6.

gurmukhi: Dwrq hY AYsO ibsn cOdsvoN Avqwr ] sMq sMbUhin suK nimq dwnv duhUM sMGwr ]7]
transliteration: Dhaarat Hai Aisau Bisan Chaudasvon Avtaar|| Sant Sanboohan(i) Soukh Namit Daanav Duhoon Sanhaar||7||
translation: In this way, Vishnu manifested himself as the fourteenth incarnation and in order to give comfort to the saints, he destroyed both these demons.7.
